<% content_for :title, "Workshop Steps - North Coast Rails Workshop" %>

<div class="card">
  <h1>North Coast Rails Workshop Steps</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Follow these step-by-step instructions to build your first Ruby on Rails web application. 
    We'll create a simple idea board where you can collect and share your thoughts!
  </p>

  <div class="highlight">
    <h3>üéØ What We're Building</h3>
    <p>A simple "Idea Board" web application where users can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Add new ideas with a title and description</li>
      <li>View all ideas in a list</li>
      <li>Edit existing ideas</li>
      <li>Delete ideas they no longer need</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="workshop-steps">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Step 1: Create Your Rails Application</h2>
    
    <p>First, let's create a new Rails application called "ideaboard":</p>
    
    <pre><code># Navigate to your projects directory
cd ~/projects  # or wherever you keep your code

# Create a new Rails app
rails new ideaboard
cd ideaboard

# Open in your text editor
code .  # if using VS Code</code></pre>

    <div class="highlight">
      <h4>üîç What just happened?</h4>
      <p>Rails generated a complete web application structure with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>app/</code> - Your application code (models, views, controllers)</li>
        <li><code>config/</code> - Configuration files</li>
        <li><code>db/</code> - Database files and migrations</li>
        <li><code>public/</code> - Static files (images, CSS, JavaScript)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Test Your Application</h3>
    <pre><code># Start the Rails server
rails server

# Open your browser and go to:
# http://localhost:3000</code></pre>

    <p>You should see the Rails welcome page! üéâ</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Step 2: Generate Your First Model</h2>
    
    <p>Now let's create an "Idea" model to store our ideas:</p>
    
    <pre><code># Generate the Idea model with title and description
rails generate model Idea title:string description:text

# Run the database migration
rails db:migrate</code></pre>

    <div class="highlight">
      <h4>üîç What just happened?</h4>
      <p>Rails created:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>app/models/idea.rb</code> - The Idea model</li>
        <li><code>db/migrate/xxx_create_ideas.rb</code> - Database migration</li>
        <li>A test file for your model</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Step 3: Create the Controller and Views</h2>
    
    <p>Generate a controller to handle web requests for ideas:</p>
    
    <pre><code># Generate the Ideas controller with standard actions
rails generate controller Ideas index show new create edit update destroy</code></pre>

    <h3>Update the Routes</h3>
    <p>Open <code>config/routes.rb</code> and replace the generated routes with:</p>
    
    <pre><code>Rails.application.routes.draw do
  root 'ideas#index'
  resources :ideas
end</code></pre>

    <h3>Implement the Controller</h3>
    <p>Open <code>app/controllers/ideas_controller.rb</code> and add:</p>
    
    <pre><code>class IdeasController < ApplicationController
  def index
    @ideas = Idea.all
  end

  def show
    @idea = Idea.find(params[:id])
  end

  def new
    @idea = Idea.new
  end

  def create
    @idea = Idea.new(idea_params)
    if @idea.save
      redirect_to @idea, notice: 'Idea was successfully created.'
    else
      render :new
    end
  end

  def edit
    @idea = Idea.find(params[:id])
  end

  def update
    @idea = Idea.find(params[:id])
    if @idea.update(idea_params)
      redirect_to @idea, notice: 'Idea was successfully updated.'
    else
      render :edit
    end
  end

  def destroy
    @idea = Idea.find(params[:id])
    @idea.destroy
    redirect_to ideas_path, notice: 'Idea was successfully deleted.'
  end

  private

  def idea_params
    params.require(:idea).permit(:title, :description)
  end
end</code></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Step 4: Create the Views</h2>
    
    <p>Now let's create beautiful views for our ideas. Update these files in <code>app/views/ideas/</code>:</p>

    <h3>Index View (app/views/ideas/index.html.erb)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;My Ideas&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;%= link_to 'New Idea', '/ideas/new', class: 'btn' %&gt;

&lt;div class="ideas-grid"&gt;
  &lt;% @ideas.each do |idea| %&gt;
    &lt;div class="idea-card"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;&lt;%= link_to idea.title, "/ideas/#{idea.id}" %&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;&lt;%= truncate(idea.description, length: 100) %&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="idea-actions"&gt;
        &lt;%= link_to 'Edit', "/ideas/#{idea.id}/edit" %&gt;
        &lt;%= link_to 'Delete', "/ideas/#{idea.id}", method: :delete, 
                    confirm: 'Are you sure?', 
                    class: 'delete-link' %&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;% end %&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>New/Edit Form (app/views/ideas/_form.html.erb)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;%= form_with model: idea do |form| %&gt;
  &lt;div class="field"&gt;
    &lt;%= form.label :title %&gt;
    &lt;%= form.text_field :title %&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field"&gt;
    &lt;%= form.label :description %&gt;
    &lt;%= form.text_area :description, rows: 5 %&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="actions"&gt;
    &lt;%= form.submit class: 'btn' %&gt;
    &lt;%= link_to 'Cancel', '/ideas' %&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;% end %&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>New View (app/views/ideas/new.html.erb)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;New Idea&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;%= render 'form', idea: @idea %&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>Show View (app/views/ideas/show.html.erb)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;&lt;%= @idea.title %&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;%= @idea.description %&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="actions"&gt;
  &lt;%= link_to 'Edit', "/ideas/#{@idea.id}/edit", class: 'btn' %&gt;
  &lt;%= link_to 'Delete', "/ideas/#{@idea.id}", method: :delete, 
              confirm: 'Are you sure?', class: 'btn btn-danger' %&gt;
  &lt;%= link_to 'Back to Ideas', '/ideas' %&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </div>

